io.requery

Annotation Type Entity


  • @Documented
 @Target(value=TYPE)
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface Entity
    Marks a type as persistable. When used with the annotation processor the processor will inspect the given class and generate a corresponding Entity class that can be used by the persistence store to perform query/create/update/delete operations. Note that only the fields in the class annotated with Entity will be persisted fields in super or sub classes will not be considered.

    • Element Detail

      • name

        public abstract String name
        Returns:
        the desired Entity name for the type. This class will be generated by the processor in the same package as the type the annotation is placed on. This name is also used as the table name unless a Table attribute is specified with a different name. Defaults to empty, the processor will remove "Abstract" prefix from the class name if it exists.
        Default:
        ""

      • model

        public abstract String model
        Returns:
        the model group this entity belongs to. Can be used to separate entities belonging to different models (databases/persistence stores) by the processor.
        Default:
        ""

      • builder

        public abstract Class<?> builder
        Returns:
        the builder class used to construct this entity if it is immutable(). Note the builder class must have a zero-argument constructor that is either package visible or public.
        Default:
        void.class

      • cacheable

        public abstract boolean cacheable
        Returns:
        true if the given object should be cached by the entity store, false otherwise.
        Default:
        true

      • extendable

        public abstract boolean extendable
        Returns:
        false if they class being annotated as entity is not extendable and the annotation processor should not generate a type extending or implementing it but instead generate only the attribute meta information. Defaults to true unless this annotation is placed on a class that is final then defaults to false.
        Default:
        true

      • immutable

        public abstract boolean immutable
        Returns:
        true if the entity object is immutable. If true the entity cannot have changeable relations and will not have any state, this implies stateless() is true. Defaults to false however if this annotation is placed in conjunction with immutable type annotations e.g. @AutoValue from Google on an object then defaults to true.
        Default:
        false

      • stateless

        public abstract boolean stateless
        Returns:
        true if the entity object should have state tracking disabled, which allows partial updates of changed values only and automatic retrieval of not loaded properties. Defaults to false, unless the entity is immutable() in which case the value is true.
        Default:
        false

      • propertyNameStyle

        public abstract PropertyNameStyle propertyNameStyle
        Defines the name style of properties in the target entity e.g. for a property 'name' and style set to PropertyNameStyle.BEAN would map to: 
        
  getName() {...}
  setName(String name) {...}
        vs for PropertyNameStyle.NONE: 
        
  name() {...}
  name(String name) {...}
        Returns:
        the name style of properties in the target entity.
        Default:
        io.requery.PropertyNameStyle.BEAN
